Saving Current Settings

Save current settings in a custom settings bank.
1Navigate to I.Q. IMAGE QUALITY SETTING in the photo menus, highlight EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING, and press MENU/OK. To save settings for movie recording, navigate to □ MOVIE SETTING in the movie menus and select CUSTOM SETTING.EDIT/SAVE
2Highlight a destination bank for cur- rent settings (C1 through C4) and press MENU/OK.I.Q. EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING CUSTOM 1 □ ASSIGNED MF CUSTOM 2 ASSIGNED CUSTOM 3 ASSIGNED そ CUSTOM 4 ASSIGNED 일 M BACK EXIT
3Highlight SAVE CURRENT SETTINGS and press MENU/OK.I.Q. C1 CUSTOM 1 SAVE CURRENT SETTINGS ▶ EDIT/CHECK SAVE THE CHANGES RESET THE CHANGES COPY RESET CUSTOM SETTING EDIT CUSTOM NAME
4Highlight OK and press MENU/OK. Current settings will be saved to the selected bank.SAVE CURRENT SETTINGS C1 CUSTOM 1 SAVE THE CHANGES OK? OK CANCEL
